<item>
            <title>[LU-4036] warning seen during ./configure --disable-server</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4036</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Now when configuring lustre to build client only the following warning is seen:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;configure: WARNING:

Disabling ldiskfs support because complete ext4 source does not exist.

If you are building using kernel-devel packages and require ldiskfs
server support then ensure that the matching kernel-debuginfo-common
and kernel-debuginfo-common-&amp;lt;arch&amp;gt; packages are installed.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the past when the --disable-server option was used no attempt was made to build ldiskfs at all and no warning was seen.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suspect this may be an unexpected side effect of the recent commit for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3953&quot; title=&quot;lustre build system improvments&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3953&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3953&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; config: move ext4 src detection to earlier phase&lt;/p&gt;</description>
